1
00:00:00,431 --> 00:00:02,833
♪♪

2
00:00:35,536 --> 00:00:38,939
Don't believe him.
He's really the evil twin.

3
00:00:38,939 --> 00:00:40,711
It's just a stupid show.

4
00:00:40,711 --> 00:00:44,215
Well, that's just
a stupid comment.

5
00:01:10,070 --> 00:01:11,302
Andrew!

6
00:01:12,803 --> 00:01:14,145
Daddy!

7
00:01:17,408 --> 00:01:18,679
Sarah: Hey!

8
00:01:18,679 --> 00:01:22,513
[Laughs]
Hey! Mmm!

9
00:01:22,513 --> 00:01:24,615
Sarah: Daddy!

10
00:01:24,615 --> 00:01:26,117
I can't believe it.

11
00:01:26,117 --> 00:01:28,058
I'm so glad
to see you guys.

12
00:01:28,058 --> 00:01:29,320
Hugo?

13
00:01:30,321 --> 00:01:31,662
You're all hairy.

14
00:01:31,662 --> 00:01:33,324
[Laughs]

15
00:01:33,324 --> 00:01:35,496
Look at you.
You must have grown
a foot.

16
00:01:35,496 --> 00:01:38,169
Just a couple of inches.

17
00:01:42,573 --> 00:01:46,076
I was gonna call,
but I wanted
to surprise you.

18
00:01:46,076 --> 00:01:47,278
Surprise.

19
00:01:47,278 --> 00:01:49,380
I was beginning
to wonder

20
00:01:49,380 --> 00:01:51,182
if we were ever gonna
see you again.

21
00:01:51,182 --> 00:01:53,684
Did you bring me
anything?

22
00:01:53,684 --> 00:01:55,686
Uh, well...Sort of.

23
00:01:55,686 --> 00:01:59,320
Hugo...why is your
luggage moving?

24
00:02:03,854 --> 00:02:05,396
I can explain.

25
00:02:07,428 --> 00:02:09,930
[Sniffing]

26
00:02:11,262 --> 00:02:13,033
Aah!

27
00:02:13,033 --> 00:02:14,565
[Screams]

28
00:02:16,167 --> 00:02:17,668
Oh, no.

29
00:02:17,668 --> 00:02:18,969
Come on, girl.

30
00:02:21,312 --> 00:02:24,014
[Grunts]
It'll be ok.

31
00:02:26,146 --> 00:02:29,320
The villagers call her
jenniquasigo,

32
00:02:29,320 --> 00:02:31,021
which means

33
00:02:31,021 --> 00:02:34,084
"little one who makes
herself look big."

34
00:02:36,457 --> 00:02:37,958
And chimps are protected.

35
00:02:37,958 --> 00:02:40,461
There's supposed to be no
hunting in ituri, but....

36
00:02:40,461 --> 00:02:42,763
That doesn't
stop the poachers.

37
00:02:42,763 --> 00:02:44,795
Their big prize
is capturing a chimp alive

38
00:02:44,795 --> 00:02:47,398
and ready to sell
on the black market.

39
00:02:47,398 --> 00:02:48,699
But sometimes
they misjudge the strength

40
00:02:48,699 --> 00:02:51,001
of the poison
in their arrows.

41
00:02:51,001 --> 00:02:54,174
That's what happened
to jennie's mother.

42
00:03:01,212 --> 00:03:02,453
[Chimps chattering]

43
00:03:26,076 --> 00:03:27,778
[Chimp screeches]

44
00:03:27,778 --> 00:03:30,241
[Speaking
native language]

45
00:03:34,915 --> 00:03:37,818
Hugo: She was pregnant,
so she was left to die.

46
00:03:37,818 --> 00:03:40,691
It's a slow death,
the muscles, organs,

47
00:03:40,691 --> 00:03:42,423
shutting down
one at a time.

48
00:03:46,797 --> 00:03:48,929
Female. Pan troglodyte.

49
00:03:48,929 --> 00:03:50,331
She's pregnant.

50
00:03:50,331 --> 00:03:53,734
[Speaking
native language]

51
00:03:53,734 --> 00:03:56,507
They say
poachers like this
ought to die.

52
00:03:58,739 --> 00:04:01,272
They used too much poison.
She's not gonna make it.

53
00:04:01,272 --> 00:04:03,113
[Speaking
native language]

54
00:04:03,113 --> 00:04:05,045
They think
you can save her.

55
00:04:05,045 --> 00:04:08,779
Tell them i'm--
I'm a ph.D. I'm not
that kind of doctor.

56
00:04:17,458 --> 00:04:19,530
I'm sorry.
There's nothing I can do.

57
00:04:27,237 --> 00:04:28,268
[Chimp grunts]

58
00:04:28,268 --> 00:04:30,571
I think she's going
into labor, doctor.

59
00:04:30,571 --> 00:04:31,702
Now?

60
00:04:31,702 --> 00:04:33,003
Yes, doctor.

61
00:04:33,003 --> 00:04:34,174
Uh, bring her
into the tent.

62
00:04:34,174 --> 00:04:35,576
I need some hot water,
I need some towels.

63
00:04:35,576 --> 00:04:37,177
Hurry, there's not
much time.

64
00:04:52,022 --> 00:04:53,564
It's a girl.

65
00:04:54,695 --> 00:04:56,597
[Speaking
native language]

66
00:04:56,597 --> 00:04:58,799
[All laugh]

67
00:04:58,799 --> 00:05:00,070
Woman: Oh...

68
00:05:00,070 --> 00:05:03,474
This baby
have powerful deefa.

69
00:05:03,474 --> 00:05:04,635
Deefa?

70
00:05:04,635 --> 00:05:08,138
Spirit...who guide this one.

71
00:05:10,741 --> 00:05:12,613
Shh.

72
00:05:19,420 --> 00:05:21,592
Jenniquasigo.

73
00:05:21,592 --> 00:05:24,324
Jenniquasigo.

74
00:05:24,324 --> 00:05:26,597
Jenniquasigo.

75
00:05:29,460 --> 00:05:32,933
Jenni...qua...sigo?

76
00:05:32,933 --> 00:05:34,465
You can
call her jennie.

77
00:05:34,465 --> 00:05:36,637
No, no, no, no,
no, no, no.

78
00:05:36,637 --> 00:05:38,469
Leah...
No.

79
00:05:38,469 --> 00:05:39,710
Wait--
no.

80
00:05:39,710 --> 00:05:41,071
Do me a favor.
Keep an eye on her.

81
00:05:41,071 --> 00:05:44,715
She's had 3 ccs
of Diazepam and I think
she has a headache.

82
00:05:44,715 --> 00:05:46,116
Leah!

83
00:05:46,116 --> 00:05:48,419
[Sarah giggles]

84
00:05:48,419 --> 00:05:51,422
She looks like
grandpa Joe.

85
00:05:51,422 --> 00:05:52,923
[Blubbers]

86
00:05:52,923 --> 00:05:54,585
Man, are you ugly.

87
00:05:54,585 --> 00:05:56,427
Ooh ooh ooh ooh.

88
00:05:57,788 --> 00:05:59,390
First, the lizard
from Madagascar,

89
00:05:59,390 --> 00:06:01,432
then that thing,
the rat from Brazil.

90
00:06:01,432 --> 00:06:02,993
Didelphis marsupialis.
It wasn't a rat.

91
00:06:02,993 --> 00:06:06,437
Whatever. It ate
Mrs. Palliser's
tulip garden.

92
00:06:07,868 --> 00:06:09,339
Leah...

93
00:06:10,601 --> 00:06:13,243
This is only temporary.
I promise.

94
00:06:20,180 --> 00:06:22,613
I missed you.

95
00:06:22,613 --> 00:06:24,485
You said 3 months
and you were gone for 8.

96
00:06:24,485 --> 00:06:28,118
After your third letter,
I just threw away the rest.

97
00:06:28,118 --> 00:06:31,462
I figured if you
died of malaria,
they'd send me a telegram.

98
00:06:31,462 --> 00:06:34,194
I know.

99
00:06:34,194 --> 00:06:37,227
I know it's hard for you
to understand, but...

100
00:06:37,227 --> 00:06:39,229
Back there in--
in the ituri,

101
00:06:39,229 --> 00:06:42,473
I was accomplishing
the most important work
of my life.

102
00:06:42,473 --> 00:06:44,274
The most important work
of your life

103
00:06:44,274 --> 00:06:46,276
is right here
under this roof.

104
00:06:46,276 --> 00:06:48,639
I'm back, Leah.

105
00:06:48,639 --> 00:06:51,782
Do you really think
you can just
waltz back in here

106
00:06:51,782 --> 00:06:54,414
with a monkey
under your arm and make
everything all right?

107
00:06:54,414 --> 00:06:56,487
She's not a monkey,
she's an ape.

108
00:06:56,487 --> 00:06:58,989
Ape.

109
00:06:58,989 --> 00:07:00,791
Ah, well, that
changes everything.

110
00:07:00,791 --> 00:07:01,792
Sarah: Daddy!

111
00:07:01,792 --> 00:07:02,953
Yes, dear?

112
00:07:02,953 --> 00:07:04,254
Jennie just took
a number 2

113
00:07:04,254 --> 00:07:06,457
on reverend palliser's
front lawn.

114
00:07:07,628 --> 00:07:09,299
I'll be right back.

115
00:07:11,502 --> 00:07:13,263
Where have I heard
that before?

116
00:07:14,304 --> 00:07:16,737
[Chattering]

117
00:07:21,271 --> 00:07:23,644
Wow. This is good.

118
00:07:25,075 --> 00:07:28,579
You know, the wukamin
consider grasshoppers
a delicacy.

119
00:07:28,579 --> 00:07:30,581
That's disgusting.

120
00:07:30,581 --> 00:07:33,884
Actually, they're not bad.
Very sweet.

121
00:07:36,056 --> 00:07:37,257
So, Andrew...

122
00:07:37,257 --> 00:07:39,429
Um, how's your
schoolwork coming?

123
00:07:39,429 --> 00:07:42,963
Um...there's this kid
named Vinnie,

124
00:07:42,963 --> 00:07:44,935
and he can
tuck in his ears,

125
00:07:44,935 --> 00:07:46,937
and it looks like
he doesn't have any.

126
00:07:46,937 --> 00:07:49,299
Your mom says
your grades

127
00:07:49,299 --> 00:07:50,971
have slipped
quite a bit this year.

128
00:07:52,843 --> 00:07:54,775
It's no big deal.

129
00:07:55,946 --> 00:07:57,578
If you want to prepare
for Harvard or Princeton,

130
00:07:57,578 --> 00:07:59,950
you've got to start now.

131
00:07:59,950 --> 00:08:01,451
Dad, I'm 12.

132
00:08:01,451 --> 00:08:03,413
You know,
when I was your age,

133
00:08:03,413 --> 00:08:04,985
I was already
a sophomore
in high school.

134
00:08:04,985 --> 00:08:06,957
Maybe I'm not
as smart as you.

135
00:08:06,957 --> 00:08:08,959
Well, we know
that's not true.

136
00:08:08,959 --> 00:08:10,460
Sorry, could you
just move the milk

137
00:08:10,460 --> 00:08:11,992
away from the ape.

138
00:08:11,992 --> 00:08:15,295
All I'm saying is you
have to start working up
to your potential.

139
00:08:15,295 --> 00:08:16,296
Maybe I don't want to.

140
00:08:16,296 --> 00:08:18,629
Andrew! That's enough.

141
00:08:20,430 --> 00:08:23,804
Hugo, can't it eat
outside?

142
00:08:23,804 --> 00:08:25,005
No, she won't
eat outside

143
00:08:25,005 --> 00:08:26,777
because she thinks
she's human.

144
00:08:28,438 --> 00:08:30,140
Can I be excused?

145
00:08:30,140 --> 00:08:31,742
Yes.

146
00:08:31,742 --> 00:08:33,213
We're not finished.

147
00:08:34,815 --> 00:08:36,086
You didn't
care about my grades

148
00:08:36,086 --> 00:08:38,348
when you were in Africa.

149
00:08:38,348 --> 00:08:39,950
[Smacks lips]

150
00:08:39,950 --> 00:08:41,151
Andrew,
that's not true--

151
00:08:41,151 --> 00:08:43,023
that's not true.

152
00:08:43,023 --> 00:08:44,955
That's not true.

153
00:09:16,587 --> 00:09:18,328
Leave me alone.

154
00:09:18,328 --> 00:09:19,890
[Whimpers]

155
00:09:58,528 --> 00:10:00,400
He seems so angry.

156
00:10:01,732 --> 00:10:05,305
He's 12 years old,
and he's growing up
without a father.

157
00:10:08,438 --> 00:10:10,140
I'm gonna go to bed.

158
00:10:28,498 --> 00:10:30,500
[Wind howling]

159
00:10:30,500 --> 00:10:33,734
[Jennie whimpers]

160
00:10:33,734 --> 00:10:35,966
[House creaks]

161
00:10:47,017 --> 00:10:49,019
[Rattling]

162
00:10:51,922 --> 00:10:56,026
[Screech]

163
00:10:57,527 --> 00:10:59,730
[Boom]

164
00:10:59,730 --> 00:11:01,792
[Jennie screeches]

165
00:11:12,102 --> 00:11:15,075
Mmm...hugo...

166
00:11:16,006 --> 00:11:19,179
I just want US
to be a family again.

167
00:11:24,584 --> 00:11:25,716
[Screeches]

168
00:11:25,716 --> 00:11:27,387
Aah! Oh!

169
00:11:27,387 --> 00:11:29,920
Honey?

170
00:11:36,566 --> 00:11:38,328
[Whimpers]

171
00:11:41,471 --> 00:11:42,702
[Yawns]

172
00:11:49,409 --> 00:11:50,680
Eech!

173
00:11:54,284 --> 00:11:55,545
Whoa!

174
00:11:58,889 --> 00:12:00,090
Oh...

175
00:12:06,556 --> 00:12:08,398
What the heck?

176
00:12:23,774 --> 00:12:25,475
Way to go, Jen.

177
00:12:25,475 --> 00:12:26,917
Hugo: I don't understand.
I locked the door.

178
00:12:26,917 --> 00:12:28,418
Sheila: Well, then,
buy a better lock.

179
00:12:28,418 --> 00:12:30,420
Or then again,
how about a cage?

180
00:12:30,420 --> 00:12:32,122
I'm not putting her
in a---

181
00:12:34,454 --> 00:12:35,826
oh...

182
00:12:35,826 --> 00:12:37,057
I'll buy a better lock.

183
00:12:37,057 --> 00:12:38,688
Oh...

184
00:12:38,688 --> 00:12:41,962
Sarah: Why are there
gummy fish in the toilet?

185
00:12:43,533 --> 00:12:45,866
Oh, my goodness.

186
00:12:45,866 --> 00:12:49,369
Either she goes
or I go.

187
00:12:54,574 --> 00:12:56,076
No, I'm serious,
Hugo.

188
00:12:56,076 --> 00:12:57,077
I know you are.

189
00:12:57,077 --> 00:12:58,348
Look,
I'll talk to Walter,

190
00:12:58,348 --> 00:12:59,709
and I'm sure
he knows somebody

191
00:12:59,709 --> 00:13:01,281
who can find
a place for her.

192
00:13:01,281 --> 00:13:03,583
You are not leaving me
here with that animal.

193
00:13:03,583 --> 00:13:05,255
There's no way.

194
00:13:05,255 --> 00:13:08,118
Leah, please.
The specimens
arrive today.

195
00:13:08,118 --> 00:13:09,920
They've been in transit
for 36 hours.

196
00:13:09,920 --> 00:13:11,421
I got to get them
into the lab
for preservation.

197
00:13:11,421 --> 00:13:13,894
I will not baby-sit
a chimpanzee.

198
00:13:13,894 --> 00:13:15,826
Look, she's probably
not hungry,

199
00:13:15,826 --> 00:13:17,597
since she ate
half the...
Kitchen already,

200
00:13:17,597 --> 00:13:19,269
and, uh,
if she gets dirty,

201
00:13:19,269 --> 00:13:21,101
uh, change her,
like when the kids
were little.

202
00:13:21,101 --> 00:13:22,602
I'll be back
before 5:00,
I promise.

203
00:13:22,602 --> 00:13:24,074
What--what--
I love you madly.

204
00:13:24,074 --> 00:13:26,636
Change her?

205
00:13:26,636 --> 00:13:28,909
You mean diaper her?!

206
00:13:28,909 --> 00:13:30,140
[Bicycle bell dings]

207
00:13:31,711 --> 00:13:34,214
This is Mandy,

208
00:13:34,214 --> 00:13:36,246
and this is Brent.

209
00:13:36,246 --> 00:13:37,717
Brent is rich.

210
00:13:37,717 --> 00:13:42,122
He drives a sports car.
He's always happy.

211
00:13:42,122 --> 00:13:44,995
Mommy says
he's a real dreamboat.

212
00:13:44,995 --> 00:13:47,057
[Chatters]

213
00:13:48,698 --> 00:13:50,060
[Screeches]

214
00:13:54,905 --> 00:13:56,566
Mommy!

215
00:13:56,566 --> 00:13:57,567
Now what?

216
00:13:57,567 --> 00:13:59,469
She bit off
Brent's head!

217
00:13:59,469 --> 00:14:01,611
Cool. Just what
I thought. All looks
and no brains.

218
00:14:01,611 --> 00:14:04,274
Sarah, sweetie,
why don't you try
reading to her?

219
00:14:04,274 --> 00:14:05,645
Reading to her?

220
00:14:05,645 --> 00:14:08,648
Meanwhile, Andrew,
would you try and fix
the basement door?

221
00:14:08,648 --> 00:14:09,649
It's already broken--

222
00:14:09,649 --> 00:14:11,121
just do it.

223
00:14:11,121 --> 00:14:12,122
[Screeches]

224
00:14:12,122 --> 00:14:13,653
Oh! Oh! Oh, no!

225
00:14:13,653 --> 00:14:15,825
Andrew, go!
Go, go get her!

226
00:14:15,825 --> 00:14:17,627
Go get her!

227
00:14:19,529 --> 00:14:21,791
[Whistling
the blue tail fly]

228
00:14:27,837 --> 00:14:29,869
[Screeches]
Whoa!

229
00:14:33,673 --> 00:14:35,906
Frank,
did you see a, um--

230
00:14:35,906 --> 00:14:38,078
Archibald.
I might have known.

231
00:14:38,078 --> 00:14:39,950
You tell your old man
I still have the scar

232
00:14:39,950 --> 00:14:42,452
from that lizard bite,
and if I get any grief

233
00:14:42,452 --> 00:14:43,653
from that baby gorilla--

234
00:14:43,653 --> 00:14:45,255
reverend palliser's?

235
00:14:45,255 --> 00:14:47,187
Thanks, frank.

236
00:14:49,319 --> 00:14:51,491
[Broken glass clinks]

237
00:14:51,491 --> 00:14:53,363
Hmm.

238
00:14:53,363 --> 00:14:55,765
I'm not paying for this!

239
00:14:55,765 --> 00:14:58,128
Aw, gee...

240
00:15:13,513 --> 00:15:16,816
Ah, 4 pink tulips,
3 daisies,

241
00:15:16,816 --> 00:15:20,450
and one little
chimpanzee.

242
00:15:22,922 --> 00:15:26,326
He--he--Hendrick...

243
00:15:28,228 --> 00:15:31,661
Hendrick!

244
00:15:31,661 --> 00:15:34,604
In his infinite
knowledge and...

245
00:15:34,604 --> 00:15:37,767
Go away!
Grace, god has--

246
00:15:40,770 --> 00:15:44,274
in his infinite
wisdom and grace...

247
00:15:44,274 --> 00:15:45,445
Oh, much better.

248
00:15:45,445 --> 00:15:48,218
Hendrick!

249
00:15:48,218 --> 00:15:50,380
Yes, dear.

250
00:15:51,781 --> 00:15:54,384
[Jennie screeches]

251
00:16:15,045 --> 00:16:18,478
The dryopithecus-hominid
link is almost conclusive now.

252
00:16:18,478 --> 00:16:22,952
Move over Richard leaky,
make way for Hugo Archibald.

253
00:16:22,952 --> 00:16:24,914
Of course, I'll need
to go back and collect
some more samples.

254
00:16:24,914 --> 00:16:26,116
To Africa?

255
00:16:26,116 --> 00:16:27,457
Yeah, I just need
a little more time
and money.

256
00:16:27,457 --> 00:16:30,960
Oh, it's scandalous,
the funding situation
in this country.

257
00:16:30,960 --> 00:16:33,063
But finding money
for your return to the ituri

258
00:16:33,063 --> 00:16:34,794
should not be a problem.

259
00:16:34,794 --> 00:16:38,498
I mean, the work
is monumental.

260
00:16:41,271 --> 00:16:42,932
Is something wrong?

261
00:16:42,932 --> 00:16:47,137
Walter, you remember
that species-isolated
chimp infant

262
00:16:47,137 --> 00:16:48,738
that I saved
when I was in Africa?

263
00:16:48,738 --> 00:16:51,081
The lowland
pan troglodyte.

264
00:16:51,081 --> 00:16:52,582
Yes.

265
00:16:52,582 --> 00:16:54,244
Pity you had
to leave it behind.

