might have for her,

707
00:41:58,316 --> 00:42:00,549
and you know
that no chimpanzee

708
00:42:00,549 --> 00:42:03,792
has ever lived with
a surrogate human family

709
00:42:03,792 --> 00:42:05,523
past the age
of adulthood,

710
00:42:05,523 --> 00:42:09,127
an age which jennie
is rapidly approaching.

711
00:42:09,127 --> 00:42:12,801
Jennie is probably
the smartest,
brightest chimpanzee

712
00:42:12,801 --> 00:42:14,032
I have ever worked with.

713
00:42:14,032 --> 00:42:16,965
She is leaving
the colony chimps
in the dust.

714
00:42:18,066 --> 00:42:19,407
Dr. Archibald,

715
00:42:19,407 --> 00:42:22,240
the tahachee center
would be willing
to pay you

716
00:42:22,240 --> 00:42:24,713
a substantial
amount of money
for jennie.

717
00:42:24,713 --> 00:42:28,416
I've been authorized
to offer you
$70,000 for her.

718
00:42:28,416 --> 00:42:30,018
As per our agreement,
Dr. Prentiss,

719
00:42:30,018 --> 00:42:31,920
