you as her father.

731
00:43:11,119 --> 00:43:13,421
She imprinted
your family
as her family.

732
00:43:13,421 --> 00:43:15,063
You've raised
a chimpanzee

733
00:43:15,063 --> 00:43:17,325
that thinks
she's human,

734
00:43:17,325 --> 00:43:19,567
but there's
a danger...

735
00:43:19,567 --> 00:43:22,000
That the imprinting
can go both ways.

736
00:43:22,000 --> 00:43:23,271
[Laughs]
What, do you think

737
00:43:23,271 --> 00:43:25,033
I think jennie
is my daughter?

738
00:43:25,033 --> 00:43:28,837
I'm speaking
to you colleague
to colleague, Hugo.

739
00:43:28,837 --> 00:43:31,940
Now, you're trying
to secure funding
for a project

740
00:43:31,940 --> 00:43:33,611
that could be
the most
important work

741
00:43:33,611 --> 00:43:36,645
in natural history
in decades.

742
00:43:36,645 --> 00:43:40,518
Do you really want
to have a feud going
with Dr. Prentiss,

743
00:43:40,518 --> 00:43:41,850
one of
the preeminent

744
00:43:41,850 --> 00:43:44,052
primatologists
in the world?

745
00:43:44,052 --> 00:43:46,554
A cage is a cage, Walter.

746
00:43:46,554 --> 00:43:48,897
Jennie doesn't belong
in a cage.

747
00:43:54,332 --> 00:43:58,606
[Sighs]

748
00:43:58,606 --> 00:44:00,939
Leah: Oh, here's
one bag for you.

749
00:44:00,939 --> 00:44:02,170
Anything good?

750
00:44:02,170 --> 00:44:04,242
Lots of refined sugar.

751
00:44:05,543 --> 00:44:06,875
[Screeches]
Oh!

752
00:44:06,875 --> 00:44:10,278
