"frank bad."

1044
00:58:34,612 --> 00:58:35,883
Say, I resent that.

1045
00:58:35,883 --> 00:58:37,915
Can she elaborate?

1046
00:58:40,147 --> 00:58:41,318
[Coos]

1047
00:58:41,318 --> 00:58:42,750
Miss trousdale:
I don't understand.

1048
00:58:42,750 --> 00:58:47,254
She's saying,
"frank bad.
Hurt Andrew."

1049
00:58:47,254 --> 00:58:49,426
Frank:
Oh, wait a minute.

1050
00:58:49,426 --> 00:58:51,999
What kind of chimpanzee
court is this?

1051
00:58:51,999 --> 00:58:53,861
It's the letter.

1052
00:58:53,861 --> 00:58:55,532
Andrew?

1053
00:58:55,532 --> 00:58:57,965
Judge: Dr. Archibald?

1054
00:58:57,965 --> 00:59:01,709
Your honor,
this is my son Andrew.

1055
00:59:01,709 --> 00:59:04,642
Andrew, is there something
you need to share with US?

1056
00:59:04,642 --> 00:59:06,243
Go ahead.

1057
00:59:06,243 --> 00:59:07,975
Jennie hurt frank

1058
00:59:07,975 --> 00:59:09,847
because
he delivers letters.

1059
00:59:09,847 --> 00:59:11,849
Letters?

1060
00:59:11,849 --> 00:59:14,121
Well, not--
not all letters.

1061
00:59:14,121 --> 00:59:15,623
One letter.

1062
00:59:15,623 --> 00:59:18,626
The letter that
said you were going
back to the ituri.

1063
00:59:18,626 --> 00:59:20,788
Back to Africa
to do more research.

1064
00:59:20,788 --> 00:59:23,160
I got the Grant.

1065
00:59:23,160 --> 00:59:26,493
And I was so angry
when you got it,

1066
00:59:26,493 --> 00:59:29,436
I tore it up.

1067
00:59:29,436 --> 00:59:32,239
And jennie
was with me,

1068
00:59:32,239 --> 00:59:35,643
and I guess
she thought
I was mad at frank.

1069
00:59:36,473 --> 00:59:37,675
Your honor,

1070
00:59:37,675 --> 00:59:40,848
I'm Dr. Pamela prentiss.
I can handle this, Pam.

1071
00:59:40,848 --> 00:59:43,080
With all
due respect, doctor,

1072
00:59:43,080 --> 00:59:44,612
I don't think you can.

1073
00:59:44,612 --> 00:59:45,813
Who is this?

1074
00:59:45,813 --> 00:59:47,454
Dr. Prentiss
is one of the most

1075
00:59:47,454 --> 00:59:49,486
celebrated primatologists
in this country.

1076
00:59:49,486 --> 00:59:51,789
She's the one
responsible for
jennie's language skills.

1077
00:59:51,789 --> 00:59:55,893
I must say, this is
quite an honor, Dr. Prentiss.

1078
00:59:55,893 --> 00:59:58,095
I've read all your books.

1079
00:59:58,095 --> 01:00:00,227
Why, thank you.

1080
01:00:00,227 --> 01:00:01,899
If the court
is interested,

1081
01:00:01,899 --> 01:00:03,831
I believe that I might
have a simple solution

1082
01:00:03,831 --> 01:00:06,233
to this somewhat
complex problem.

1083
01:00:06,233 --> 01:00:07,775
I'm all ears.

1084
01:00:07,775 --> 01:00:08,936
But, your honor, wo--

1085
01:00:08,936 --> 01:00:12,579
Mr. Russo, Dr. Archibald,
Dr. Prentiss,

1086
01:00:12,579 --> 01:00:15,082
if I may please see you
in my chambers

1087
01:00:15,082 --> 01:00:16,914
for a short recess.

1088
01:00:16,914 --> 01:00:18,786
Bailiff: All rise!
[Jennie cackles]

1089
01:00:41,909 --> 01:00:43,270
Where are the kids?

1090
01:00:43,270 --> 01:00:45,112
I took them
back to school.

1091
01:00:47,044 --> 01:00:50,147
So what did the judge say?

1092
01:00:55,452 --> 01:00:59,026
[Softly]
Oh, Hugo, no.

1093
01:01:02,189 --> 01:01:03,190
It's ok.
It's all right.

1094
01:01:03,190 --> 01:01:04,661
I mean, it's
better this way.

1095
01:01:04,661 --> 01:01:07,094
I don't think...

1096
01:01:07,094 --> 01:01:08,495
I don't think
it's fair that
you should have to

1097
01:01:08,495 --> 01:01:09,797
take care
of the kids
and jennie

1098
01:01:09,797 --> 01:01:12,339
while I'm in--

1099
01:01:12,339 --> 01:01:15,542
while you're what?
[Sighs]

1100
01:01:17,705 --> 01:01:19,807
You're not actually
considering going back.

1101
01:01:19,807 --> 01:01:21,008
This is
important, Leah.

1102
01:01:21,008 --> 01:01:22,509
Yes, it is, Hugo.

1103
01:01:24,251 --> 01:01:26,583
Yes, it is.

1104
01:01:28,185 --> 01:01:30,017
They're going to
be devastated.

1105
01:01:30,017 --> 01:01:32,589
First jennie,
and then you.

1106
01:01:37,294 --> 01:01:40,397
We were just starting to
feel like a family again.

1107
01:02:08,195 --> 01:02:09,957
I haven't been up here
in a while.

1108
01:02:09,957 --> 01:02:11,198
[Coos]

1109
01:02:12,199 --> 01:02:15,132
You did a good job.

1110
01:02:15,132 --> 01:02:17,264
It's held up well.

1111
01:02:21,168 --> 01:02:23,410
Jennie...

1112
01:02:26,413 --> 01:02:29,316
Jennie, go with Pam today.

1113
01:02:29,316 --> 01:02:30,547
[Whimpering]

1114
01:02:30,547 --> 01:02:32,249
No.

1115
01:02:32,249 --> 01:02:34,321
Hugo no go.

1116
01:02:34,321 --> 01:02:36,924
[Moans]

1117
01:02:39,486 --> 01:02:43,060
You know, a good friend
once told me that you
have a powerful deefa...

1118
01:02:44,361 --> 01:02:46,233
And I believe him.

1119
01:02:48,896 --> 01:02:50,968
Jennie? Jennie?

1120
01:02:52,239 --> 01:02:54,601
Jennie?

1121
01:03:01,408 --> 01:03:02,749
Jennie?

1122
01:03:04,051 --> 01:03:08,255
Ah. Ahh.

1123
01:03:08,255 --> 01:03:10,587
Hi, there.
How are you?

1124
01:03:13,260 --> 01:03:15,262
She's as strong
as 7 men, doctor.

1125
01:03:15,262 --> 01:03:18,465
What's she
going to be like
in a year or 2?

1126
01:03:20,427 --> 01:03:22,769
She needs a controlled,
disciplined environment.

1127
01:03:24,801 --> 01:03:26,803
She belongs
to science now.

1128
01:03:26,803 --> 01:03:29,106
We both know
it's for the best.

1129
01:03:29,106 --> 01:03:32,039
You mean, the best
for Dr. Pamela prentiss.

1130
01:03:33,040 --> 01:03:36,613
Dr. Archibald, we both
have our careers,

1131
01:03:36,613 --> 01:03:39,586
and I have dedicated
my entire life to mine.

1132
01:03:39,586 --> 01:03:42,419
And no matter what you
and your family might think,

1133
01:03:42,419 --> 01:03:45,592
I care about jennie
an awful lot.

1134
01:03:47,754 --> 01:03:49,626
[Jennie cackles]

1135
01:03:59,606 --> 01:04:02,739
[Jennie screeches]

1136
01:04:20,827 --> 01:04:22,960
Dad...

1137
01:04:22,960 --> 01:04:23,961
Hey, kiddo.

1138
01:04:23,961 --> 01:04:26,293
Check this out.

1139
01:04:26,293 --> 01:04:28,265
That's fantastic.

1140
01:04:28,265 --> 01:04:31,338
I pulled my average
up an entire
letter grade.

1141
01:04:31,338 --> 01:04:33,400
Wait'll I tell Jen.

1142
01:04:34,471 --> 01:04:36,343
Andrew--

1143
01:04:36,343 --> 01:04:38,946
where's Jen?

1144
01:04:40,377 --> 01:04:41,748
Jennie?

1145
01:04:41,748 --> 01:04:44,781
Jen. Jennie!

1146
01:04:46,453 --> 01:04:48,455
Hey, jennie!

1147
01:04:48,455 --> 01:04:50,387
Andrew!

1148
01:04:52,559 --> 01:04:53,560
Andrew.

1149
01:04:53,560 --> 01:04:55,993
Jennie! Jennie.

1150
01:04:55,993 --> 01:04:57,664
Honey?

1151
01:04:59,666 --> 01:05:01,398
[Shouting]
Jennie!

1152
01:05:01,398 --> 01:05:04,831
Jennie! Jennie.

1153
01:05:04,831 --> 01:05:05,973
Where is she?

1154
01:05:05,973 --> 01:05:07,074
The judge thought it
best for her to

1155
01:05:07,074 --> 01:05:08,705
live at the tahachee center.

1156
01:05:08,705 --> 01:05:10,807
No! How could you?!

1157
01:05:13,780 --> 01:05:15,542
Andrew!

1158
01:05:17,484 --> 01:05:20,287
Andrew!

1159
01:05:27,894 --> 01:05:29,926
Yeah. Yeah,
he's been missing
for 5 hours.

1160
01:05:29,926 --> 01:05:31,198
Don't tell me
that I can't file

1161
01:05:31,198 --> 01:05:32,899
a missing persons
report.

1162
01:05:32,899 --> 01:05:35,462
He's only
12 years old.

1163
01:05:35,462 --> 01:05:38,335
No, not the chimp,
my son.

1164
01:05:38,335 --> 01:05:39,406
Forget the chimp.

1165
01:05:39,406 --> 01:05:41,508
Forget that I even
brought the chimp up.

1166
01:05:42,469 --> 01:05:44,771
Please, officer,
I just need you

1167
01:05:44,771 --> 01:05:47,114
to help me
find my little boy.

1168
01:05:48,745 --> 01:05:50,177
Yes. I appreciate
that. I do.

1169
01:05:50,177 --> 01:05:53,520
Thank you very much.
Yes. Thank you.

1170
01:05:55,782 --> 01:05:58,225
I've searched everywhere.
I don't understand
what he's thinking.

1171
01:05:58,225 --> 01:05:59,456
I've called
all his friends,

1172
01:05:59,456 --> 01:06:00,957
the neighbors,
the police.

1173
01:06:00,957 --> 01:06:03,060
This is all my fault.
You can say that again.

1174
01:06:03,060 --> 01:06:04,831
I know where Andrew went.

1175
01:06:04,831 --> 01:06:06,063
I never should have
let that woman take her

1176
01:06:06,063 --> 01:06:07,434
without at least
a good-bye.

1177
01:06:07,434 --> 01:06:09,836
He went to
the hot cheese center.

1178
01:06:10,737 --> 01:06:11,999
What did you say?

1179
01:06:11,999 --> 01:06:14,001
The hot cheese center.

1180
01:06:14,001 --> 01:06:16,843
Melted cheese?

1181
01:06:16,843 --> 01:06:18,175
What do you mean,
sweetie?

1182
01:06:18,175 --> 01:06:21,608
He went to see jennie.

1183
01:06:21,608 --> 01:06:24,011
The tahachee center!

1184
01:06:24,011 --> 01:06:25,012
That's what I said.

1185
01:06:25,012 --> 01:06:26,983
Of course!
Uh, grab the keys.

1186
01:06:49,976 --> 01:06:52,209
[Jennie whimpers]

1187
01:06:57,214 --> 01:06:59,086
Jennie hungry?

1188
01:07:01,618 --> 01:07:04,621
I brought your favorites.

1189
01:07:06,753 --> 01:07:09,756
Jennie, eat.

1190
01:07:09,756 --> 01:07:11,628
[Jennie whimpers]

1191
01:07:11,628 --> 01:07:12,829
Please?

1192
01:07:24,571 --> 01:07:27,414
I understand.

1193
01:07:59,206 --> 01:08:00,607
[Snort]

1194
01:08:04,651 --> 01:08:07,554
[Snoring]

1195
01:08:16,563 --> 01:08:18,625
Jennie?

1196
01:08:18,625 --> 01:08:20,367
Jennie!

1197
01:08:50,096 --> 01:08:51,398
Jennie.

1198
01:08:54,431 --> 01:08:56,533
Jennie?

1199
01:08:57,264 --> 01:08:59,936
Jennie!

1200
01:08:59,936 --> 01:09:01,137
[Jennie screeches]

1201
01:09:01,137 --> 01:09:02,669
Jennie.

1202
01:09:07,214 --> 01:09:09,075
Jennie--

1203
01:09:12,279 --> 01:09:13,980
jennie, you knew
I'd see you again.

1204
01:09:18,925 --> 01:09:20,757
All right,
let's get outta here.

1205
01:09:34,140 --> 01:09:36,172
Oh!

1206
01:09:36,172 --> 01:09:37,744
We can't get out.

1207
01:09:37,744 --> 01:09:39,506
It's locked
from the outside.

1208
01:09:39,506 --> 01:09:41,278
What am I
gonna do now?

1209
01:09:41,278 --> 01:09:43,250
Oooh.

1210
01:10:29,095 --> 01:10:30,927
[Thunder]

1211
01:10:39,005 --> 01:10:41,308
Mom, dad?

1212
01:10:41,308 --> 01:10:43,840
Shh.
Everything's all right.

1213
01:10:43,840 --> 01:10:45,211
Hey.

1214
01:10:46,172 --> 01:10:47,414
Hey.

1215
01:10:50,747 --> 01:10:51,748
Where's Jen?

1216
01:10:51,748 --> 01:10:53,249
She's just fine.

1217
01:10:53,249 --> 01:10:54,721
We can't leave her here.

1218
01:10:54,721 --> 01:10:56,052
We're not going to.

1219
01:10:56,052 --> 01:10:57,424
She's
going back home.

1220
01:10:57,424 --> 01:10:59,225
Really?

1221
01:11:03,290 --> 01:11:05,732
I decided to
go back to Africa.

1222
01:11:05,732 --> 01:11:06,833
[Thunder]

1223
01:11:06,833 --> 01:11:08,264
One last trip.

1224
01:11:08,264 --> 01:11:10,597
You're gonna
take her back,
aren't you?

1225
01:11:10,597 --> 01:11:12,599
We think
we might be able

1226
01:11:12,599 --> 01:11:14,301
to return Jenny
to the ituri.

1227
01:11:14,301 --> 01:11:15,902
What about the poachers?

1228
01:11:15,902 --> 01:11:18,475
Well, the land that
jennie was born in

1229
01:11:18,475 --> 01:11:20,276
was recently
made a sanctuary.

1230
01:11:20,276 --> 01:11:22,779
She'll be protected.

1231
01:11:22,779 --> 01:11:23,780
You know,
very few apes

1232
01:11:23,780 --> 01:11:25,181
have ever returned
to the wild

1233
01:11:25,181 --> 01:11:27,454
after having
lived in captivity.

1234
01:11:28,955 --> 01:11:30,286
Unless, of course,
you are able to

1235
01:11:30,286 --> 01:11:34,220
find jennie's family group,
and maybe--

1236
01:11:34,220 --> 01:11:37,023
that they might just
accept her,

1237
01:11:37,023 --> 01:11:38,925
and she, them.

1238
01:11:38,925 --> 01:11:42,068
I'd sure like it
if you came along.

1239
01:11:42,068 --> 01:11:44,100
Me?

1240
01:11:44,100 --> 01:11:46,302
All of US.
[Giggles]
Mmm.

1241
01:11:47,404 --> 01:11:49,235
All right!
Oh, I can't wait to go.

1242
01:11:49,235 --> 01:11:52,278
Hugo: Yeah, when you see it,
you'll meet my friend kwele.

1243
01:11:52,278 --> 01:11:54,240
All right. Thanks.
Let's go now.

1244
01:11:54,240 --> 01:12:00,046
[African chorale sings]

1245
01:12:16,433 --> 01:12:17,434
[Jennie coos]

1246
01:12:17,434 --> 01:12:20,437
Heh heh heh.
Welcome, my old friend.

1247
01:12:20,437 --> 01:12:22,969
Kwele, it's been
a long time.

1248
01:12:22,969 --> 01:12:24,340
Yes, it has.
[Laughs]

1249
01:12:24,340 --> 01:12:25,372
This is my family.

1250
01:12:25,372 --> 01:12:26,773
Hey, kwele.
Hey.

1251
01:12:26,773 --> 01:12:28,044
Nice to finally
meet you, kwele.

1252
01:12:28,044 --> 01:12:29,876
Pleasure to meet you.

1253
01:12:29,876 --> 01:12:31,047
Ahh!

1254
01:12:31,047 --> 01:12:33,450
This one's a little young
for research assistant.

1255
01:12:33,450 --> 01:12:34,581
[Laughs]
[Laughs]

1256
01:12:34,581 --> 01:12:35,782
And who is this?

1257
01:12:35,782 --> 01:12:38,124
This beef grow big!

1258
01:12:38,124 --> 01:12:40,657
What that tell you?
Big trouble, no?

1259
01:12:40,657 --> 01:12:42,889
[Laughs]
Yeah, they're
all big trouble.

1260
01:12:42,889 --> 01:12:46,493
Welcome. Come, come.

1261
01:13:28,835 --> 01:13:31,077
[Cooing, chattering]

1262
01:15:06,502 --> 01:15:08,575
Andrew: My father,
being a man of science,

1263
01:15:08,575 --> 01:15:11,077
believed in a natural
order of all things.

1264
01:15:11,077 --> 01:15:12,879
He believed that
the world is a place

1265
01:15:12,879 --> 01:15:16,583
to be comprehended,
dissected, and classified.

1266
01:15:16,583 --> 01:15:18,444
But jennie
taught him something:

1267
01:15:18,444 --> 01:15:19,515
That we see the world

1268
01:15:19,515 --> 01:15:21,087
not only
through our eyes,

1269
01:15:21,087 --> 01:15:23,820
but through our hearts.

1270
01:15:23,820 --> 01:15:26,292
It's time to go.

1271
01:15:44,611 --> 01:15:46,573
[Jennie coos]

